<subSubSection id="B2D6B2DC4116E9126BCDD402FC9E2088" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="FA73E1574116E9126BCDD402FB1520AC" blockId="62.[151,1436,618,751]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454116E9126BCDD402FEDD20E5" bold="true" box="[151,266,618,643]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Ovipositor sheath very long (3.0– 
<quantity id="3D344CB24116E91269CAD402FD3E20E4" box="[656,745,618,642]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3 mm</quantity>
), fore wing 1.20–1.25 times longer than ovipositor (
<figureCitation id="62F7FDD24116E9126E77D402FA5820E4" box="[1325,1423,618,642]" captionStart="FIGURES 95–104" captionStartId="73.[151,264,1637,1660]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,193,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-32@73.[151,1436,193,1616]" captionTargetPageId="73" captionText="FIGURES 95–104. Ovipositor sheaths of Xyela species. All figures at same scale. Legend: HT—holotype; PT—paratype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261378" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261378/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Fig. 104</figureCitation>
); valvula 3 compressed in cross-section, with acicular tip, without defined sensilla field; harpes longer than wide; medial lobe of penis valve strongly asymmetrical, inclined toward base of valviceps (
<figureCitation id="62F7FDD24116E9126F09D4DAFB6220AC" box="[1107,1205,690,714]" captionStart="FIGURES 136–145" captionStartId="77.[151,263,1745,1768]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1706]" captionTargetId="figure-41@77.[151,1436,193,1725]" captionTargetPageId="77" captionText="FIGURES 136–145. Penis valves of Xyela species: X. curva group, X. julii group (part). Figs 138–139 and 141 reproduced from Blank et al. (2005)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5261388" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5261388/files/figure.png" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Fig. 140</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA73E1574116E9126B9DD4BEFC9E2088" blockId="62.[151,1436,618,751]" box="[199,841,726,751]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454116E9126B9DD4BEFE5B2089" bold="true" box="[199,396,726,751]" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Species included</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="3DCC9AD44116E9126AC0D4BEFD982088" authorityName="Blank &amp; Shinohara &amp; Altenhofer" authorityYear="2013" box="[410,591,726,750]" class="Insecta" family="Xyelidae" genus="Xyela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="63" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rasnitsyni">
<emphasis id="C8B83D454116E9126AC0D4BEFD982088" box="[410,591,726,750]" italics="true" pageId="62" pageNumber="63">Xyela rasnitsyni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the East Palearctic.
</paragraph>
